1:1 COMMENT "# arbprec_constants.z \u{2014} literal-coercion ergonomics demo."
1:58 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# Numeric literals (and constant expressions built from them) coerce"
3:69 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# losslessly to a target numeric type at typed-location boundaries"
4:67 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# without needing an explicit `.u8` / `.u32` / `.i32` suffix."
5:62 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "#"
6:2 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# A literal that doesn't fit the target is rejected at compile time"
7:68 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# with a literal-aware diagnostic (\"literal value 300 cannot be"
8:64 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# losslessly stored in u8 (range 0..255)\") \u{2014} no runtime overflow."
9:66 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "#"
10:2 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "# Constant arithmetic folds at unbounded Python-int precision, so"
11:66 EOL "\n"
12:1 COMMENT "# intermediate values are NOT range-checked against any concrete"
12:65 EOL "\n"
13:1 COMMENT "# numeric type \u{2014} only the final value is checked at the coercion"
13:65 EOL "\n"
14:1 COMMENT "# boundary. So an expression whose intermediate would overflow even"
14:68 EOL "\n"
15:1 COMMENT "# u64 still works if the final fits the destination."
15:53 EOL "\n"
16:1 COMMENT "#"
16:2 EOL "\n"
17:1 COMMENT "# Explicit suffixes still work; they remain the user-facing escape"
17:67 EOL "\n"
18:1 COMMENT "# hatch when the surrounding context does not pin the type."
18:60 EOL "\n"
19:1 EOL "\n"
20:1 COMMENT "# Call-arg coercion: bare 8-bit byte literals into a u8 parameter."
20:67 EOL "\n"
21:1 LABEL "push_byte"
21:10 COLON ":"
21:11 WS " "
21:12 FUNCTION "function"
21:20 WS " "
21:21 BRACEOPEN "{"
21:22 LABEL "b"
21:23 COLON ":"
21:24 WS " "
21:25 REFID "u8"
21:27 BRACECLOSE "}"
21:28 WS " "
21:29 IS "is"
21:31 WS " "
21:32 BRACEOPEN "{"
21:33 EOL "\n"
22:1 WS "    "
22:5 COMMENT "# Body is a no-op \u{2014} the call sites below are the point."
22:60 EOL "\n"
23:1 BRACECLOSE "}"
23:2 EOL "\n"
24:1 EOL "\n"
25:1 COMMENT "# Call-arg coercion: u64 parameter accepts an arbitrarily wide"
25:63 EOL "\n"
26:1 COMMENT "# intermediate."
26:16 EOL "\n"
27:1 LABEL "push_u64"
27:9 COLON ":"
27:10 WS " "
27:11 FUNCTION "function"
27:19 WS " "
27:20 BRACEOPEN "{"
27:21 LABEL "x"
27:22 COLON ":"
27:23 WS " "
27:24 REFID "u64"
27:27 BRACECLOSE "}"
27:28 WS " "
27:29 IS "is"
27:31 WS " "
27:32 BRACEOPEN "{"
27:33 WS " "
27:34 BRACECLOSE "}"
27:35 EOL "\n"
28:1 EOL "\n"
29:1 COMMENT "# Function-return coercion: the body `200 + 100 - 250` folds to 50"
29:67 EOL "\n"
30:1 COMMENT "# (which fits u8) \u{2014} the intermediate 300 does not block the coercion"
30:69 EOL "\n"
31:1 COMMENT "# because the final value is range-checked at the return boundary,"
31:67 EOL "\n"
32:1 COMMENT "# not in the middle of the expression."
32:39 EOL "\n"
